## When to use
When you need to analyze your system's overall network traffic usage and want a real-time overview of bandwidth consumption.

## Approach
Utilize the `shell_exec` tool to execute the `bmon` command, which provides an interactive monitoring facility for network interfaces. This approach allows for observing real-time traffic statistics including incoming and outgoing data rates.

## Example
```sh
shell_exec "bmon -c 1"
```
This example uses the `shell_exec` tool to run a shell command that initiates bmon in curses mode, displaying an interactive view of network traffic every second. This is useful for gaining real-time insights into bandwidth usage.

## Pitfalls
- Ensure necessary utilities like `bmon` are installed on your system.
- Be aware that `bmon -c 1` might not provide a continuous update if run in non-interactively; consider running it interactively or with appropriate options for continuous monitoring.